service_type.description: The type of service related to the transaction (e.g., Ads credit purchase)

payment_mode.description: The method of payment used (e.g., card)

payment_status.description: The status of the payment (e.g., Successful)

direction.description: The direction of the transaction (e.g., DEBIT)

timestamp.description: Timestamp of when the transaction occurred (ISO 8601 format)

remarks.description: Additional remarks or notes about the transaction

allow_primary.description: Indicates if the category allows primary assignment.

is_leaf.description: True if this is a leaf category (has no subcategories), false otherwise.

is_primary.description: True if this is considered a primary category.

level.description: The hierarchical level of the category.

mapping_enabledd.description: Indicates if mapping is enabled for this category. (Note: potential typo in original data: 'mapping_enabledd' instead of 'mapping_enabled')

name.description: The name of the category (e.g., 'Children Magazines').

parent_category_id.description: The ID of the parent category, if applicable.

date.description: Unix timestamp for the invoice date

start_date.description: Unix timestamp for the start of the invoice period

end_date.description: Unix timestamp for the end of the invoice period

cn_urls.description: List of URLs for credit notes, or null if none

order_id.description: Associated order ID, or null if not applicable
